<hr/>

Hi.

I hope to use helper functions in some controllers with action2 type.
But in controllers, I can't handle custom exits from helpers.

For example, a helper calls the custom exit defined as below:
```
  exits: {
    notFoundInHelper: {
      description: 'Not found in helper',
    },
    unauthorizedInHelper: {
      description: 'Unauthorized in helper',
    },
  },
```
And the part of invoking exits in a helper is as below:
```
...
try {
  const result = await MyModel.find(opts);

  if (!_.isEmpty(result)) {
    return exits.notFoundInHelper();
  }

  return exits.success(result);
} catch (ex) {
  return exits.error(ex);
}
...
```

In my controller, I define the custom exit in the controller code as below:
```
...
  exits: {
    notFoundInController: {
      statusCode: 404,
      description: 'Not found in controller',
    },
    unauthorizedInController: {
      statusCode: 401,
      description: 'Unauthorized in controller',
    },
  },
...
```

And I hope to handle `notFoundInHelper` at controller in the right way, but I don't know how I can.
How can I know which custom exits is invoked at try - catch block?
```
...
try {
  const result = sails.helpers.getMyModel(opts);
  return exits.success(result);
} catch (ex) {
  // How can I know this exception is 'notFoundInHelper'?
  if (<is this exception is notFoundInHelper>) {
    return exits.notFoundInController();
  }
  return exits.error(ex);
}
```
Or is there any other way to handle this?

